    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-09T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170. Your 278, June 8, 3 p.m., and Department’s 22, December 21, 7 p.m., which
                    quotes final paragraph of Department’s 367, December 21, 7 p.m., to Tokyo.<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d461fn50">Telegrams Nos. 22 and 367 not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department has sent the following telegram to Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Department authorizes approach under conditions and along lines of final
                            paragraph Department’s 367, December 21, 7 p.m.”<note n="51"
                                xml:id="d461fn51">For note presented to the Japanese Foreign Office,
                                see telegram No. 822, June 11, 10 p.m., from the Consul General at
                                Shanghai, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_599">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 599</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
